#lang strike

;;; ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
;;; THE CLOCKLESS DISCIPLINE — CONSTITUTIONAL
;;;
;;; PURPOSE: This strike table IS the law. It is struck before
;;; any new work begins. If you are reaching for sequential
;;; logic, a clock, Python, iteration, or "step 1 then step 2,"
;;; strike this circuit first. The current will remind you.
;;;
;;; Shape determines what comes next. Not the clock.
;;; The s-expression IS the circuit. The pairs ARE the wires.
;;; The nesting IS the topology. The strike IS the current.
;;; The residue IS what the current did.
;;;
;;; Writing the s-expression IS wiring the circuit.
;;; Specification IS instantiation. Articulation IS implementation.
;;; The trace function IS the electricity following the wires.
;;;
;;; A dotted pair (a . b) is a wire. Current in at a, out at b.
;;; A transformation is a circuit board made of wires.
;;; Zoom in on any component: more wires. All the way down to
;;; () — presence — current — the thing that actually flows.
;;;
;;; There is no step 1 and step 2. There is a shape, and the
;;; current fills it. Nesting depth resolves inside-out not
;;; because of a rule but because current can't reach outer
;;; wires until it's flowed through inner wires.
;;;
;;; GROUNDING STANDARD:
;;; Only computed or verified facts go in parentheses.
;;; Narrative, interpretation, meaning go in ;;; comments.
;;; If labels carry all the content, it's noise not science.
;;;
;;; ENFORCEMENT:
;;; 1. lint — no Racket keywords
;;; 2. audit — no empty vacuum tubes
;;; 3. test — all programs run
;;; 4. every domain needs a cross-domain composition
;;; 5. every pair must be computed or verified
;;; ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

(clockless-discipline

  ;;; Source: the question every builder must answer
  (what-determines-what-comes-next)

  ;;; Target: the answer that never changes
  (shape-determines-what-comes-next)

  ;;; Vacuum tube: the constitutional chain
  ((what-determines-what-comes-next . not-the-clock)
   (not-the-clock . not-sequence)
   (not-sequence . not-a-program-counter)
   (not-a-program-counter . the-shape-of-the-circuit)
   (the-shape-of-the-circuit . wires-are-pairs)
   (wires-are-pairs . topology-is-nesting)
   (topology-is-nesting . current-follows-wires)
   (current-follows-wires . current-is-trace)
   (current-is-trace . presence-is-electricity)
   (presence-is-electricity . shape-determines-what-comes-next)))
